If you haven't pretended
to leave your kids behind
when they wouldn't get in
the motherf*ing car, are
you even a parent?

going to bed in your 20's:
fall into bed in whatever you're wearing.
going to bed in your 30's:
start the dishwasher. let the pets out.
lock up the house.
make sure the kids are breathing.
go to the bathroom, take makeup off.
brush & floss your teeth. apply moisturiser,
eye serum, brown spots cream & wrinkle eraser.
take vitamins. make your to-do list
for the next day. try to sieep & roll around
for an hour over-thinking your life.

university, proved that prolonged screen time can
